HEADWORD: Divorcement
<hw>Di*vorce"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Dissolution of
the marriage tie; divorce; separation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let him write her a <qex>divorcement</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Deut.
xxiv. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>divorcement</qex> of our written from our spoken
language.</q> <rj><qau>R. Morris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divorcer</ent>⟦br⟧
